It was a beautiful father-and-son bonding time for Davido who took time off to unwind with his son, Ifeanyi Adeleke. In a video shared via the Instagram page of the DMW boss, he can be seen with his 2-year-old son outside his premises getting set to race while the security men watched on with admiration. The father of three in the video could be heard saying; “Future Nigeria Olympic Gold medalist…” While Davido spoke, his young son kept struggling to break free from his grip so he could race off. Eventually he was set free to do his thing after the words; “Let’s go.” The lil champ zoomed off with his father right behind him. - Advertisement - Davido swiftly overtook Ifeanyi, grabbed, lifted him off the ground and held him close to his chest. The video has earned the “Fem” singer admiration from celebrities alongside his fans and followers who also gushed over little Ifeanyi. Pretty Mike said: “This na Super 30 BG Horse Power turbocharged.” Actress Toyin Adewale stated: “Awwww, God bless you son.”   PSquare never paid for me for shows – May D     Obi Cubana meets Lagos hawker, restates scholarship offer     Why I dropped out of varsity, by Lagos hawker who gave…   Singer Ycee wrote: “This clip gon make me hit it raw. I want one now.” TheOrangeNerd said: “I can see the gold already.” Yetunde Bakare wrote: “He can’t wait to run.” temmy.fred stated: “We like anything you do ORI-ADE.” Rico Swavey said: “Cute lil baby.” drey_xii wrote: “Notice how he has time for all his kids? Man has his priorities straight.” myrasfeer said: “Little man couldn’t wait to race. He’s so cute.” kolamide_ stated: “Lol man is running like Sterling.” muktar.zinat93 wrote: “Our very own Usain Bolt.” __onyinyechukwu__ said: “See me smiling soo hard.”